    <has_dmc>Yes</has_dmc>
  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Patients with triple negative metastatic breast cancer (HER2-, PR-, ER-) will receive
      bevacizumab, paclitaxel and capecitabine as a first line of treatment (possibility to have
      received adjuvant chemotherapy).
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
